==Other diagram files==
These files can be used to create diagrams for explaining certain positions or indicating piece movement.
<!--Hiding this because it still needs some tweaking:*[[File:Shogi bck44.png|22px]] '''bck''' - black square for dividing diagrams (''bck'' is for 'black')-->
<!--Hiding this because it still needs some tweaking:*[[File:Shogi ha44.png|22px]] '''ha''' - divide diagram into sections (''ha'' is for 'half')-->
:*[[File:Shogi rah22.svg|22px]] ‎ '''rah''' - indicate start position for a move one square to the right (''rah'' is for 'right arrow half')
:*[[File:Shogi rat22.svg|22px]] '''rat''' - indicate movement from left to right (''rat'' is for 'right arrow tip')
:*[[File:Shogi ras22.svg|22px]] '''ras''' - indicate start position from right to left (''ras'' is for 'right arrow start')
:*[[File:Shogi lra22.svg|22px]] '''lra''' - indicate movement from right to left or left to right (''lra'' is for 'left right arrow')
:*[[File:Shogi lah22.svg|22px]]  '''lah''' - indicate start position for a move one square to the left (''lah'' is for 'left arrow half')
:*[[File:Shogi lat22.svg|22px]] '''lat''' - indicate movement from right to left (''lat'' is for 'left arrow tip')
:*[[File:Shogi las22.svg|22px]] '''las''' - indicate start positiong for movement from left to right (''las'' is for 'left arrow start')
:*[[File:Shogi uah22.svg|22px]] '''uah''' - indicate start position for a move one square upward (''kadl'' is for 'up arrow half')
:*[[File:Shogi uat22.svg|22px]] '''uat''' - indicate movement from bottom to top (''uat'' is for 'upward arrow tip')
:*[[File:Shogi uas22.svg|22px]] '''uas''' - indicate start position for movement from bottom to top (''uas'' is for 'up arrow start')
:*[[File:Shogi uda22.svg|22px]] '''uda''' - indicate movement from bottom to top or top to bottom (''uda'' is for 'up down arrow')
:*[[File:Shogi dah22.svg|22px]] '''dah''' - indicate start position for a move one square downward (''dah'' is for 'down arrow half')
:*[[File:Shogi das22.svg|22px]] '''das''' - indicate start position for movement from top to bottom (''das'' is for 'down arrow start')
:*[[File:Shogi dat22.svg|22px]] '''dat''' - indicate movement from top to bottom (''dat'' is for 'downward arrow tip')
:*[[File:Shogi durh22.svg|22px]] '''durh''' - indicate start position for a move one square diagonally upward to the right (''durh'' is for 'diagonal up right half')
:*[[File:Shogi dau22.svg|22px]] '''dau''' - indicate movement diagonally upward to the right (''dau'' is for 'diagonal arrow upward')
:*[[File:Shogi daus44.png‎|22px]] '''daus''' - indicate start position for movement diagonally upward to right (''daus'' is for 'diagonal arrow upward start')
:*[[File:Shogi da44.png‎|22px]] '''da''' - indicate movement diagonally left to right (''da'' is for 'diagonal arrow')
:*[[File:Shogi ddlh22.svg|22px]] '''ddlh''' - indicate start position for a move one square diagonally downward to the left (''ddlh'' is for 'diagonal down left half')
:*[[File:Shogi dad22.svg|22px]] '''dad''' - indicate movement diagonally downward to the left (''dad'' is for 'diagonal arrow downward')
:*[[File:Shogi dads44.png‎|22px]] '''dads''' - indicate start position for movement diagonally downward to left (''dads'' is for 'diagonal arrow downward start')
:*[[File:Shogi dulh22.svg|22px]] '''dulh''' - indicate start position for a move one square diagonally upward to the left (''dulh'' is for 'diagonal up left half')
:*[[File:Shogi daau44.png‎|22px]] '''daau''' - indicate movement diagonally upward to left (''daau'' is for 'diagonal arrow averse upward')
:*[[File:Shogi daaus44.png‎|22px]] '''daaus''' - indicate start position for movement diagonally upward to left (''daaus'' is for 'diagonal arrow averse upward start')
:*[[File:Shogi daa44.png‎|22px]] '''daa''' - indicate movement diagonally right to left (''daa'' is for 'diagonal arrow averse')
:*[[File:Shogi ddrh22.svg|22px]] '''ddrh''' - indicate start position for a move one square diagonally downward to the right (''ddrh'' is for 'diagonal down right half')
:*[[File:Shogi daad44.png‎|22px]] '''daad''' - indicate movement diagonally downward to right (''daad'' is for 'diagonal arrow averse downward')
:*[[File:Shogi daads44.png‎|22px]] '''daads''' - indicate start position for movement diagonally downward to right (''daads'' is for 'diagonal arrow averse downward start')
:*[[File:Shogi kar22.svg|22px]] '''kar''' - indicate movement of knight upward to the right (''kar'' is for 'knight arrow right')
:*[[File:Shogi kal22.svg|22px]] '''kal''' - indicate movement of knight upward to the left (''kal'' is for 'knight arrow left')
:*[[File:Shogi kadr22.svg|22px]] '''kadr''' - indicate movement of knight downward to the right (''kadr'' is for 'knight arrow down right')
:*[[File:Shogi kadl22.svg|22px]] '''kadl''' - indicate movement of knight downward to the left (''kadl'' is for 'knight arrow down left')
:*[[File:Shogi ddl22.svg|22px]] '''ddl''' - indicate movement of silver downward to the left (''ddl'' is for 'diagonal down left')
:*[[File:Shogi ddr22.svg|22px]] '''ddr''' - indicate movement of silver downward to the right (''ddr'' is for 'diagonal down right')
:*[[File:Shogi dul22.svg|22px]] '''dul''' - indicate movement of silver downward to the left (''dul'' is for 'daigonal up left')
:*[[File:Shogi dur22.svg|22px]] '''dur''' - indicate movement of silver downward to the right (''dur'' is for 'diagonal up right')
:*[[Image:shogi_yy22.svg|22px]] '''yy''' - highlighted yellow square (''yy'' is for 'yellow')
:*[[File:Shogi gr22.svg|22px]] '''gr''' -  highlighted gray square (''gr'' is for 'gray')

==Examples==
The following are examples of the types of diagrams which can be created.

===Even game between players of same rank===
Diagrams for such positions typically show "sente" at the bottom of the board, and "gote" at the top. Relevant information such as player names, tournament names, etc. may be entered into parameters <2> and <84> if desired.   

